57.4	The_Lives_of_Others	The Lives of Others	The Lives of Others (German: ) is a 2006 German drama film, marking the feature film debut of filmmaker Florian Henckel von Donnersmarck. The film involves the monitoring of the cultural scene of East Berlin by agents of the Stasi, the GDR's secret police. It stars Ulrich MÃ¼he as Stasi Captain Gerd Wiesler, Ulrich Tukur as his boss Anton Grubitz, Sebastian Koch as the playwright Georg Dreyman, and Martina Gedeck as Dreyman's lover, a prominent actress named Christa-Maria Sieland.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/9f/Leben_der_anderen.jpg/215px-Leben_der_anderen.jpg
